## Description {#details}

This file provides Any, a non-template class modeled in the spirit of std::any.

The idea is to provide a type-safe replacement for C&#39;s void&#42;. It can hold a value of any copy-constructible copy-assignable type

<Link id="l00126" /><CodeLine lineNumber="126"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00127" /><CodeLine lineNumber="127"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Define the type id and initialize with a non-zero value.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00128" /><CodeLine lineNumber="128"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Initializing with a zero value means the variable can end up in either the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00129" /><CodeLine lineNumber="129"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// .data or the .bss section. This can lead to multiple definition linker errors</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00130" /><CodeLine lineNumber="130"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// when some object files are compiled with a compiler that puts the variable</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00131" /><CodeLine lineNumber="131"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// into .data but they are linked to object files from a different compiler that</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00132" /><CodeLine lineNumber="132"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// put the variable into .bss. To prevent this issue from happening, initialize</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00133" /><CodeLine lineNumber="133"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the variable with a non-zero value, which forces it to land in .data (because</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00134" /><CodeLine lineNumber="134"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// .bss is zero-initialized).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00135" /><CodeLine lineNumber="135"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// See also https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/62270</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00136" /><CodeLine lineNumber="136"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">template</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &lt;</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">typename</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> T&gt; </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">char</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> Any::TypeId&lt;T&gt;::Id = 1;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00137" /><CodeLine lineNumber="137"></CodeLine>
